# Collaborative documents (shared-document)

> Merit-based collaborative editing: official block text, proposed variants, voting with заслуги, manual vs auto apply. Canonical product/architecture: `docs/prd/shared-document/business-approved-tz.md`; PRD folder: `docs/prd/shared-document/`.

---

## Concept

- **Document** (`documents` collection): belongs to a **community** (`communityId`). Types: `imageOfFuture` (one per community — ОБ), `description` (one per project community), `custom` (only when `documentsMode === 'all'`).
- **Sections → blocks**: embedded in the document. Each **block** has stable `id`, `officialContent`, optional voting anchor `currentWaveStartedAt`, edit metadata (`officialContentReason`: `initial` | `vote` | `admin`).
- **Variant** (`document_block_variants`): proposed alternative text for one block; `status`: `open` → `closed-winner` / `closed-not-winner` → optional `applied`; `withdrawn` if author retracts.
- **Votes**: reuse **`Vote`** with **`targetType === 'document-variant'`** and `targetId` = variant id (same quota/wallet/community rules as other weighted votes; Future Vision may require comment text — see `votes.router` / @business-future-vision.mdc).

---

## Community settings (documents hub)

- **`Community.settings.documentsMode`**: `'off'` | `'visionOrDescriptionOnly'` | `'all'` — controls whether only seeded OB/description docs exist vs arbitrary custom documents.
- **`documentCreators`**, **`documentVariantCost`**, **`documentVotingDurationHours`**, **`documentDefaultMode`**, **`documentAutoApplyTimerHours`** — economy and defaults for variants/waves (see `community.schema` / shared-types).

---

## Apply modes (`MeriterDocument.mode`)

| Mode | Behaviour |
|------|-------------|
| **`manual`** | After a wave closes, a **`closed-winner`** variant must be **applied** by author/admin via **`documentVariants.applyVotingWinner`** (or **applyOpenAsAdmin** for override). |
| **`auto`** | After **`finalizeExpiredWaveOnBlock`**, if there is a **`closed-winner`** with **positive rating**, **`applyVariantToOfficial`** runs automatically with synthetic actor **`MERITER_DOCUMENT_AUTO_APPLY_USER_ID`** (`meriter-actors.constant.ts`). |

Manual UI apply is rejected when `mode !== 'manual'` for **`applyVotingWinner`**.

---

## Voting waves and cron

- **Wave open**: while **`DocumentVariantService`/document helpers** consider the block’s voting window open (`currentWaveStartedAt` + `votingDurationHours`), finalize does nothing.
- **Finalize**: **`finalizeExpiredWaveOnBlock(documentId, blockId)`** — ranks open variants by rating (tie-break `proposedAt`), assigns `closed-winner` / `closed-not-winner`, clears wave anchor; then **`tryAutoApplyWinner`** if `mode === 'auto'`.
- **Periodic sweep**: **`DocumentWaveCronService`** (`*/5 * * * *`) calls **`runPeriodicWaveSweep()`** — discovers `(documentId, blockId)` pairs with **`open`** variants, skips blocks still voting, otherwise **`finalizeExpiredWaveOnBlock`**.
- **Trigger on propose**: proposing a variant also calls **`finalizeExpiredWaveOnBlock`** first so elapsed waves close before a new open variant is added.

---

## Economics

- **Propose variant**: fee via **`document_variant_proposal`** (quota/wallet rules in **`DocumentVariantService`**); aligns with global burn for fees (see @business-merits.mdc / fees).
- **Max variant body length**: **5000** characters (API trim); rich HTML from WYSIWYG counts toward the limit.

---

## Mirror to legacy community fields (§5.3)

- OB (`type === 'imageOfFuture'`) and project description (`type === 'description'`): **`mirrorOfficialTextToCommunityIfApplicable`** updates **`futureVisionText`** / **`description`** on **`Community`**.
- For **OB**, mirror also calls **`PublicationService.updateFutureVisionPostContent`** on the **`future-vision`** hub so feed cards stay aligned with the document (same path as direct `Community.futureVisionText` edits in **`CommunityService.updateCommunity`**).
- **No `imageOfFuture` document** on hub communities (`typeTag`: `future-vision`, `marathon-of-good`, `team-projects`). Bootstrap + startup migration skip them; stray hub OB rows are soft-deleted on migration.
- **Startup migration:** `CollaborativeDocumentsMigrationService` (`onModuleInit`), revision in `platform_settings.collaborativeDocumentsMigrationRevision` (`COLLABORATIVE_DOCUMENTS_MIGRATION_REVISION`). Manual: `pnpm --filter @meriter/api migrate:collaborative-documents`.
- **`concatOfficialPlainText`** builds plain text from block **`officialContent`**; **HTML is stripped** for mirror (**`stripHtmlForMirror`**) so legacy fields stay readable plain text while the document stores rich content.

---

## Variant references (§17)

- Up to **10** links per variant: `url` (http/https, ≤2000 chars), `summary` (required, ≤280), optional `stance` (`pro` | `con`).
- API: `normalizeDocumentVariantReferences` in `domain/common/document-variant-references.util.ts`; passed via `documentVariants.propose` `references` array.
- Web: `DocumentVariantReferencesEditor` on propose form; `DocumentVariantReferencesList` on variant cards. References stay on the variant record after apply (not copied to official block).

## Block history (§19)

- Each change to **`officialContent`** appends **`block.editHistory`**: `previousContent`, `changedBy`, `changedAt`, `reason` (`initial` | `vote` | `admin`), optional `variantId` when `reason === 'vote'`.
- Populated on **`applyVariantToOfficial`** and **`applyAdminOverride`** (not retroactively for pre-migration blocks).

## Document structure (§7.4, §20.2)

- **Who**: community **lead**, document **author**, or **superadmin** (`assertCanManageDocument`).
- **tRPC** (`documents`): `addSection`, `updateSection`, `removeSection`, `addBlock`, `updateBlock`, `removeBlock`.
- **Guards**: cannot remove the only section or the only block in the document; removing block/section with non-empty **`officialContent`** requires **`confirmLossOfOfficial: true`**; open variants on removed blocks → **`withdrawn`**; OB/description docs re-mirror community plain text after structure change.
- **Web**: document toolbar (add section / add block to last section); per-block `DocumentBlockStructureControls` (section title, block type, remove with confirm).

## Server HTML (§24.9)

- **`sanitizeDocumentHtml`** (`api/.../common/utils/sanitize-document-html.ts`) runs on **`propose`** and **`applyAdminOverride`**; allowlist aligned with web **`DocumentRichContent`**.

## tRPC (high level)

| Namespace | Procedures |
|-------------|------------|
| **`documents`** | `listByCommunity`, `getById`, `getOfficialByType`, **`updateMeta`**, **`applyAdminOverride`**, structure mutations (`addSection`, `updateSection`, `removeSection`, `addBlock`, `updateBlock`, `removeBlock`) |
| **`documentVariants`** | `listByBlock`, `propose`, `withdraw`, `applyVotingWinner`, `applyOpenAsAdmin`, **`closeVotingWaveOnBlock`**, **`deleteVariant`** |
| **`votes`** | `create` / `createWithComment` with **`document-variant`** |

---

## Web routes

- Community hub link + **`/meriter/communities/[id]/documents`** (list), **`/meriter/communities/[id]/documents/[documentId]`** (detail).
- Proposal/editor: TipTap **`RichTextEditor`**; display: **`DocumentRichContent`** (client DOMPurify); API sanitizes on save.
- Document page (lead): official reason badge, wave timer, collapse variants, admin override dialog, block history, apply open variant, delete variant, close voting wave.

---

## Notifications (§20.7, MVP)

Emitted from **`DocumentVariantService`** via **`NotificationService`**:

| Type | When |
|------|------|
| **`document_variant_won`** | Variant becomes **`closed-winner`** after wave finalize (positive rating) |
| **`document_variant_applied`** | Variant applied to **`officialContent`** |
| **`document_block_admin_override`** | **`applyAdminOverride`** closes open variants on the block (authors notified, not the actor) |

Redirect: **`/meriter/communities/{communityId}/documents/{documentId}`**. Metadata: `communityId`, `documentId`, `documentTitle`, `blockId`, `communityName`, `inviteTargetIsProject`.

**Votes on variants:** comment required in **all** communities (`votes` router); not only **`future-vision`**.

